diseases.name: Breast Cancer
diseases.description: Malignant tumor arising from breast epithelial cells, often associated with ERBB2 overexpression.

diseases.name: Melanoma
diseases.description: Chromosomal anaplasma of diploid hyperchromic melanocytes characterized by primitive neuroectodermal cells.

diseases.name: Carcinoma
diseases.description: General term for cancer that arises in a specific tissue or organ, e.g., lung carcinoma, ovary carcinoma, etc.

diseases.name: Sarcomas
diseases.description: Malignant tumors arising from soft tissues (e.g., muscles, tendons, and ligaments) composed of mesenchymal cells.

diseases.name: Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia
diseases.description: Chronic lymphocyte leukemia characterized by acute leukemia in the bone marrow due to chronic antigen exposure.

diseases.name: Inflammatory Bowel Disease
diseases.description: Group of related diseases involving chronic inflammation of the gastrointestinal tract and/or its secondary complications.

diseases.name: Diabetes Mellitus
diseases.description: A group of metabolic disorders characterized by chronic hyperglycemia, usually due to insulin resistance or deficiency.

diseases.name: Cardiovascular Diseases
diseases.description: Group of diseases affecting the heart and circulatory system, including hypertension, atherosclerosis, and heart attacks.

diseases.name: Neurodegenerative Diseases
diseases.description: Chronic brain disorders characterized by progressive decline in cognitive function due to the degeneration of neurons within the central nervous system.

diseases.name: Cystic Fibrosis
diseases.description: Genetic disorder causing thick, sticky mucus in the lungs and digestive tract; typically results from mutations in the CFTR gene.

associations.description: BRCA1 mutation is a known predisposition factor for breast cancer.
BRCA1 mutation is associated with increased risk of sarcomas.
TP53 mutation is a known predisposition factor for breast cancer and other cancers.
EGFR mutation is associated with melanoma, particularly in BRAF-mutated or tyrosine kinase inhibitor-naive settings.
KRAS mutation is a known predisposition factor for acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL).
PIK3CA mutation is associated with inflammatory bowel disease (IBD).
EGFR mutation is a known predisposition factor for type 2 diabetes mellitus.
ATM kinase mutations are associated with cardiovascular diseases in certain contexts.
H2A.Z mutation is a known predisposition factor for neurodegenerative diseases.
